post_text: New Jersey's highest court has for years seen how systemic racism has prevented woman of color from serving on the court. Today we take a step in the right direction with the nomination Fabiana Pierre-Louis, who, if confirmed, will be the first black woman ever to serve on the NJ Supreme Court. We must continue the push to change systemic and systematic practices that keep us out of these spaces.
text: New Jersey's highest court has for years seen how systemic racism has prevented woman of color from serving on the court. Today we take a step in the right direction with the nomination Fabiana Pierre-Louis, who, if confirmed, will be the first black woman ever to serve on the NJ Supreme Court. We must continue the push to change systemic and systematic practices that keep us out of these spaces.

post_text: We were happy to participate in the 16 days of activism!!!
shared_text:
Zonta Club of Essex County is with Alicia Pinnix Robinson and 10 others.
November 26, 2019 at 10:59 AM ¬∑

Day 2 of #16Days of Activism Against Gender-Based Violence.
The students at Queen City Academy Charter School in Plainfield, under the leadership of Mrs. Danielle West-Augustin, kicked off the 2019 16 Days of Activism campaign by wearing orange ribbons. Zonta Club of Essex County member Theresa Perry Lewis spoke to the Middle School Students about the campaign and invited them to participate in a Essay/Poster Contest.
The school will have other projects during the 16 days and beyond.

Day 2 of #16Days of Activism Against Gender-Based Violence.
The students at Queen City Academy Charter School in Plainfield, under the leadership of Mrs. Danielle West-Augustin, kicked off the 2019 16 Days of Activism campaign by wearing orange ribbons. Zonta Club of Essex County member Theresa Perry Lewis spoke to the Middle School Students about the campaign and invited them to participate in a Essay/Poster Contest.
The school will have other projects during the 16 days and beyond.

Happy New Year #QCACS family! January will be full of new programs that will begin at QCACS and I'm excited to welcome back our scholars on January 2nd!

As always we want to thank our families for choosing QCACS as their school choice option.
